167
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:36,529
Don't you know
which syndicate we're from--

168
00:11:38,656 --> 00:11:40,574
Listen closely, kid.

169
00:11:42,618 --> 00:11:44,537
We men can make our living,

170
00:11:45,538 --> 00:11:48,290
and walk around pompously
with our heads held high,

171
00:11:50,292 --> 00:11:52,795
only thanks to all the women

172
00:11:53,546 --> 00:11:55,965
who protect our stupid pride.

173
00:11:59,301 --> 00:12:01,554
Maybe it's no use talking to
low-level men like you.

174
00:12:02,763 --> 00:12:04,849
Why don't you take me to your boss?

175
00:12:08,853 --> 00:12:10,938
I should discipline you punks.

176
00:12:12,064 --> 00:12:13,399
Let's go! This is trouble!

177
00:12:13,482 --> 00:12:15,234
Why is the boss of the Oya syndicate here?

178
00:12:18,237 --> 00:12:19,238
Excuse us!

179
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:26,162
The boss of the Oya syndicate?

180
00:12:29,623 --> 00:12:31,792
Does that mean he's...

181
00:12:34,128 --> 00:12:36,172
Mr. Oya's father?

182
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:38,507
Are you all right?

183
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:41,093
I'm fine. Thank you.

184
00:12:41,427 --> 00:12:44,430
I thought if I mentioned
calling the police, they'd stop.

185
00:12:44,513 --> 00:12:45,723
The chair...

186
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:47,725
Never mind about the chair.

187
00:12:48,976 --> 00:12:50,811
